{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":"SQL Data Notebook:\n\nNormal SQL:"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"tags":["sql"]},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/markdown":"|FIRSTNME|LASTNAME|SALARY|\n|----|----|----|\n|CHRISTINE|HAAS|152750|\n|MICHAEL|THOMPSON|94250|\n|SALLY|KWAN|98250|\n|JAMES|SMITH|81200|\n|JOHN|GEYER|80175|\n|IRVING|STERN|72250|\n|EVA|PULASKI|96170|\n|ROBERT|BROWN|71200|\n|EILEEN|HENDERSON|89750|\n|THEODORE|SPENSER|86150|\n|VINCENZO|LUCCHESSI|66500|\n|SEAN|O'CONNELL|49250|\n|DOLORES|QUINTANA|73800|\n|HEATHER|NICHOLLS|48400|\n|BRUCE|ADAMSON|75200|\n|ELIZABETH|PIANKA|70200|\n|MASATOSHI|YOSHIMURA|74600|\n|MARILYN|SCOUTTEN|81300|\n|JOSE|PEREZ|49200|\n|DAVID|WALKER|82300|\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":"\nSELECT FIRSTNME, LASTNAME, SALARY \nFROM JFYO1.EMPLOYEE;\n"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"tags":["sql"]},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/markdown":"|DEPTNO|DEPTNAME|\n|----|----|\n|A00|SPIFFY COMPUTER SERVICE DIV.|\n|B01|PLANNING|\n|C01|INFORMATION CENTER|\n|D01|DEVELOPMENT CENTER|\n|D11|MANUFACTURING SYSTEMS|\n|D21|ADMINISTRATION SYSTEMS|\n|E01|SUPPORT SERVICES|\n|E11|OPERATIONS|\n|F22|HR|\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":"SELECT DEPTNO, DEPTNAME\nFROM JFYO1.DEPARTMENT;\n"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"tags":["sql"]},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/markdown":"|FIRSTNME|LASTNAME|DEPTNAME|SALARY|\n|----|----|----|----|\n|CHRISTINE|HAAS|SPIFFY COMPUTER SERVICE DIV.|152750|\n|SALLY|KWAN|INFORMATION CENTER|98250|\n|EVA|PULASKI|ADMINISTRATION SYSTEMS|96170|\n|MICHAEL|THOMPSON|PLANNING|94250|\n|EILEEN|HENDERSON|SUPPORT SERVICES|89750|\n|THEODORE|SPENSER|OPERATIONS|86150|\n|DAVID|WALKER|OPERATIONS|82300|\n|MARILYN|SCOUTTEN|ADMINISTRATION SYSTEMS|81300|\n|JAMES|SMITH|DEVELOPMENT CENTER|81200|\n|JOHN|GEYER|SUPPORT SERVICES|80175|\n|BRUCE|ADAMSON|DEVELOPMENT CENTER|75200|\n|MASATOSHI|YOSHIMURA|MANUFACTURING SYSTEMS|74600|\n|DOLORES|QUINTANA|INFORMATION CENTER|73800|\n|IRVING|STERN|MANUFACTURING SYSTEMS|72250|\n|ROBERT|BROWN|MANUFACTURING SYSTEMS|71200|\n|ELIZABETH|PIANKA|MANUFACTURING SYSTEMS|70200|\n|VINCENZO|LUCCHESSI|SPIFFY COMPUTER SERVICE DIV.|66500|\n|SEAN|O'CONNELL|HR|49250|\n|JOSE|PEREZ|ADMINISTRATION SYSTEMS|49200|\n|HEATHER|NICHOLLS|PLANNING|48400|\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":"SELECT \n    E.FIRSTNME,\n    E.LASTNAME,\n    D.DEPTNAME,\n    E.SALARY\nFROM JFYO1.EMPLOYEE E\nJOIN JFYO1.DEPARTMENT D\n  ON E.WORKDEPT = D.DEPTNO\nORDER BY E.SALARY DESC;"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{"tags":["sql"]},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/markdown":"|WORKDEPT|FIRSTNME|LASTNAME|SALARY|RANK_IN_DEPT|\n|----|----|----|----|----|\n|A00|CHRISTINE|HAAS|152750|1|\n|A00|VINCENZO|LUCCHESSI|66500|2|\n|B01|MICHAEL|THOMPSON|94250|1|\n|B01|HEATHER|NICHOLLS|48400|2|\n|C01|SALLY|KWAN|98250|1|\n|C01|DOLORES|QUINTANA|73800|2|\n|D01|JAMES|SMITH|81200|1|\n|D01|BRUCE|ADAMSON|75200|2|\n|D11|MASATOSHI|YOSHIMURA|74600|1|\n|D11|IRVING|STERN|72250|2|\n|D11|ROBERT|BROWN|71200|3|\n|D11|ELIZABETH|PIANKA|70200|4|\n|D21|EVA|PULASKI|96170|1|\n|D21|MARILYN|SCOUTTEN|81300|2|\n|D21|JOSE|PEREZ|49200|3|\n|E01|EILEEN|HENDERSON|89750|1|\n|E01|JOHN|GEYER|80175|2|\n|E11|THEODORE|SPENSER|86150|1|\n|E11|DAVID|WALKER|82300|2|\n|F22|SEAN|O'CONNELL|49250|1|\n"},"metadata":{}}],"source":"SELECT \n    WORKDEPT,\n    FIRSTNME,\n    LASTNAME,\n    SALARY,\n    RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY WORKDEPT ORDER BY SALARY DESC) AS RANK_IN_DEPT\nFROM JFYO1.EMPLOYEE;"},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":"Data Notebooks are commonly used in data analysis and Machine Learning using python, R, Kotlin, and other programming languages.\n\nThe main difference with db2 notebooks is that when using python we move the data to the code and when using db2 notebooks we move the code to the data. This means that we can run SQL queries directly on the data without having to move it to a different environment.\n\nIn python we need to extract the data from the database, load it into a pandas dataframe, and then run our analysis on it. In db2 notebooks we can run our SQL queries directly on the data and get the results back without having to move it to a different environment. Or programm the data access using python and then run the SQL queries directly on the data."},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":"First we need to extract the data."}],"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"DB2 for IBM i","name":"db2i"},"language_info":{"name":"sql","file_extension":"sql"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0}